      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 13.62,
      "end": 21.4,
      "text": "Recorded by Annie Coleman in St. Louis, Missouri on January 13, 2006.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 22.7,
      "end": 27.56,
      "text": "ASAP's Fables. The Boys and the Frogs.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 29.04,
      "end": 45.6,
      "text": "Some mischievous boys were playing on the edge of a pond, and, catching sight of some frogs swimming about in the shallow water, they began to amuse themselves by pelting them with stones, and they killed several of them.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 46.6,
      "end": 60.04,
      "text": "At last, one of the frogs put his head out of the water and said, Oh stop, stop! I beg of you! What a sport to you is death to us.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 62.26,
      "end": 66.1,
      "text": "End of the Boys and the Frogs.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
